  "text": "Intracellular production of ROS and/or reactive nitrogen species was measured according to [CITATION_1] . Briefly, 15 mM 5-(and-6)-chloromethyl-2',7'-dichlorodihydrofluorescein diacetate (CM-H 2 DCFDA; Molecular Probes), dissolved in ethanol, was added to the cell suspension. This nonpolar compound is actively taken up by cells and converted by esterases into 29,79-dichlorodihydrofluorescein, a nonfluorescent molecule, which is rapidly oxidized to the highly fluorescent 29,79-dichlorofluorescein by intracellular peroxides. The cells were incubated for 15 min in the dark, and then excess dye was removed by extensive washing of the cells with fresh culture medium, and the cells were observed within 30 min of treatment under a Zeiss 710 confocal microscope. The 29,79-dichlorofluorescein was imaged as described by [CITATION_2] . These experiments were repeated at least two times.",
